(97, 1, '2023-12-02 17:33:10', '2023-12-02 17:33:10', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A difficult question, that can only be answered conventionally. I worked ten years as an actor. Ten years as a developer. Three years of writing and studying poetry... The next ten years as a nomad (I hope)… while running this enlighting blog (at least for me). </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I studied a bit of Sociology, more of Industrial Management, mostly Dramatic Art and Cinematography. I did and I am doing my best studies alone. While I\'m not connected on the internet, I reads books, I have a big library in my house at Paleo Faliro. Lately, I\'ve been reading mostly literature and philosophy.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I can answer what my worldly identity is, I can describe what I am not or what interests me at this time. My texts are original and written in Greek (originally). I practice and study the art of writing every day, but although greek writer, I am currently learning Italian and Spanish, I am strongly interested in the rhythm of any language, its music, its poetry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the beginning of 2020, I started writing poetry every day. Until then, I \'ve writen childhood and teenage poems, but also verses that were melodized in stage plays. I now have two books of poetry collections in Greek editions: The Confinement of a Dream (published by Evmaros, 2022) and Parapera (published by Kedros, 2022). My third collection is ready and waiting for the right path to the printer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My name is Nikos Drosakis, I don\'t wear the tie of a professional, I have several professional IDs. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>My land is any place that touches my poetic self and I touch it poetically, without being consuming it as a spectacle.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Who am I', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '96-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-12-02 17:33:10', '2023-12-02 17:33:10', '', 96, 'https://nomadpoetry.com/?p=97', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
